  <answer><![CDATA[<div class="c-page-content">
<p>Due to Canada's northerly location, the winter snowfall across its resorts holds a good track record, so you will find plenty of snow during the ski season. <a data-udi="umb://document/3f77e79eea2d4582a9acb3c89406dc88" href="/{localLink:umb://document/3f77e79eea2d4582a9acb3c89406dc88}" title="Banff">Banff</a> and <a data-udi="umb://document/7cf5e06f2ccd4cf8b8f46d06ca905a75" href="/{localLink:umb://document/7cf5e06f2ccd4cf8b8f46d06ca905a75}" title="Lake Louise">Lake Louise</a> have very fluffy dry snow as it's located so far from the sea - unbeatable on powder days.</p>
</div>]]></answer>
